                        "content": "When would the nurse advise a client being prescribed fluoxetine hydrochloride for depression to take the medication?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nFluoxetine hydrochloride is an antidepressant and is administered in the early morning for depression so that the client will experience an elevated mood during the daytime hours. In addition, fluoxetine can cause insomnia, so taking the medication early in the day will prevent interference with sleep. The other options are incorrect for depression. For bipolar disorder, this medication is given once daily in the evening hours.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Psychiatric: Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitors (SSRIs)\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Mood Disorders\nIntegrated Process: Teaching and Learning\nPriority Concepts: Mood and Affect, Patient Education\nStrategies: Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, fluoxetine hydrochloride. Knowledge of the medication's action and use will direct you to the correct option. Recalling that fluoxetine can cause insomnia will assist in answering correctly.",
                        "id": "6e6270c918164464a14c25f06523fa82",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
