                        "content": "The health care provider is planning to prescribe a medication for a client with major depression. Which medication should the nurse expect to be prescribed?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nParoxetine is an antidepressant used in the treatment of major depression. Diazepam and lorazepam are benzodiazepines and are used to treat anxiety. Phenobarbital is a barbiturate used for the short-term treatment of insomnia.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Recognize Cues\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Psychiatric: Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitors (SSRIs)\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Mood Disorders\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Analysis\nPriority Concepts: Mood and Affect, Clinical Judgment\nStrategies: Comparable or Alike Options, Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, medication used to treat major depression. Eliminate options 1 and 2 because they are comparable or alike and are benzodiazepines. To select from the remaining options, it is necessary to know that paroxetine is an antidepressant used in the treatment of major depression.",
