                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nSpecific side and adverse effects related to fluoxetine include central nervous system and gastrointestinal system dysfunction. Fluoxetine affects the gastrointestinal system by causing nausea and vomiting, cramping, and diarrhea. Renal dysfunctions, dry mouth, and excessive sweating are not side and adverse effects associated with this medication.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Recognize Cues\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Psychiatric: Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitors (SSRIs)\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Mood Disorders\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Assessment\nPriority Concepts: Clinical Judgment, Safety\nStrategies: Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, specific side and adverse effects of fluoxetine. It is necessary to remember that this medication causes gastrointestinal problems. This will direct you to the correct option.",
