                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "A client with depression has a prescription for sertraline (Zoloft). The nurse should withhold the medication and question the prescription if which is documented in the client's record?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nSertraline is a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor. Fatal reactions may occur if sertraline is administered concurrently with phenelzine, a monoamine oxidase inhibitor (MAOI). MAOIs would be stopped at least 14 days before initiation of sertraline therapy. Likewise, sertraline would be stopped at least 14 days before initiation of MAOI therapy. The other options are incorrect.\n\nClient Needs: Safe and Effective Care Environment\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Psychiatric: Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitors (SSRIs)\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Mood Disorders\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Implementation\nPriority Concepts: Clinical Judgment, Safety\nStrategies: Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, the need to withhold the medication. Knowledge of the interactions and contraindications to the use of sertraline is needed to answer this question. Remember that fatal reactions may occur if sertraline is administered concurrently with an MAOI.\n ",
